{
 "_readme": [
  "Competitor-mapped public rate card (docs/pricing-rate-card.md). Apply after sign-off:",
  "1) POST /api/v1/admin/price-plan   with .plan  -> note the returned id",
  "2) For each .rules[]: set pricePlanId to that id, POST /api/v1/admin/price-plan/rule",
  "All prices USD/hour (platform base currency must be USD).",
  "GPU rules are additive on top of the CPU/RAM component rules — see the rate card's",
  "calibration note before changing values. gpu_model aliases follow the pci-alias form.",
  "kubernetes_cluster is the managed-k8s CONTROL-PLANE fee only, priced per CP replica",
  "(attrs: display_name/version/status/endpoint/cp_replicas/node_groups — see",
  "internal/cloud/billingresource/kubernetescluster.go). A cluster's worker VMs, volumes",
  "and API load balancer live in the customer's own keystone tenant and already bill via",
  "the existing instance/volume/load_balancer rules — never add k8s rules for them here",
  "(double-charge). Billing starts once the control-plane endpoint exists; the rate below",
  "is a placeholder until the plan-§6 CP-pricing decision (free CP vs paid HA vs flat fee).",
  "_pendingRules are NOT applied by the steps above. kubernetes_cluster sits there (matching the commented-out twin in price-plan-seed.sql) until the plan-§6 CP-pricing decision; move it into .rules to activate, and update the SQL twin in the same change."
 ],
